items.name: Multi-Agent-Stock-Market-Analysis-and-Financial-Insights
items.description: This project demonstrates the implementation of a multi-agent system designed to analyze stock market trends, provide financial insights, and perform web-based data retrieval. Each agent in the system is tailored for specific roles, leveraging tools and APIs to deliver accurate and actionable outputs.

items.name: Mental-Health-Analysis
items.description: Description An analysis of mental health from 2016 to 2020, exploring factors like gender, age, treatment-seeking behavior, and workplace mental health benefits. It includes data cleaning, transformation, and visualization to uncover insights and support mental wellness in professional environments worldwide.

items.name: RoboticsThreeLawsSimulator
items.description: This project is a simulator based on Isaac Asimov's Three Laws of Robotics. It demonstrates how robots make decisions in scenarios with humans, considering the number of humans in danger, available robots, and actions. The goal is to illustrate the impact of these laws in real-world situations.

items.name: Heating-Load-Predicting
items.description: This project involves predicting the heating load of buildings based on a variety of features such as building size, orientation, and environmental factors. The goal is to develop accurate and interpretable models that can assist in energy efficiency planning and optimization.

items.name: Game-of-snake-with-python
items.description: **Snake Game** is a classic game where the player controls a snake to eat objects (usually apples) and grow longer. The goal is to avoid the snake biting its own tail or hitting the screen edges. The game gets harder as the snake grows and moves faster. It remains a popular retro game.
